'''Sivaganga''', also known as '''Sivagangai''', is a city and a [[municipality]] in [[Sivaganga district]] in the [[India]]n [[States and territories of India|state]] of [[Tamil Nadu]]. It is the administrative headquarters of Sivaganga district. 

==Geography==
Sivaganga is located at {{coor d|9.87|N|78.48|E|}}<ref>[http://www.fallingrain.com/world/IN/25/Sivaganga.html Falling Rain Genomics, Inc - Sivaganga]</ref>. It has an average elevation of 102&nbsp;[[metre]]s (334&nbsp;[[foot (unit of length)|feet]]).

==Demographics==
[[As of 2001]] India [[census]]{{GR|India}}, Sivaganga had a population of 40,129. Males constitute 50% of the population and females 50%. Sivaganga has an average literacy rate of 82%, higher than the national average of 59.5%: male literacy is 86%, and female literacy is 77%. In Sivaganga, 11% of the population is under 6 years of age.

